com.alexgilleran.icesoap.request

Interface SOAP11Request<ResultType>

  • Type Parameters:
    ResultType - The type of the object to retrieve from this request. If the type is a List, you may want to consider using ListRequest instead.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Request<ResultType,SOAP11Fault>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SOAP11ListRequest<ResultType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SOAP11ListRequestImpl, SOAP11RequestImpl

    public interface SOAP11Request<ResultType>
extends Request<ResultType,SOAP11Fault>
    Encapsulates all the code for making a SOAP Request - to use, create an object that implements the SOAP11Observer class (generally this is easiest using anonymous objects from the activity or fragment) and attach it using the Request#registerObserver(SOAP11Observer) method. Then invoke Request.execute() - the request will be performed on a background thread, and methods of the SOAP11Observer will be called on the UI thread. This extension of the standard Request interface already specifies the default SOAP11Fault - it is the same as the v1.0.0 Request interface.
    Author:
    Alex Gilleran
